cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper involves cross-modal knowledge fusion using embeddings from text knowledge graphs and images. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category deals with natural language processing and understanding, which is relevant to the text knowledge graph part of the paper.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category deals with image processing and analysis, which is relevant to the image part of the paper.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): This sub-category deals with techniques for retrieving relevant information from large collections of data, which is relevant to the knowledge fusion aspect of the paper.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category deals with the development of algorithms and models that can learn from data, which is relevant to the embedding approaches used in the paper.
- cs.MM (Multimedia): This sub-category deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data, which is relevant to the cross-modal nature of the paper.
